TITLE: McCarthy told 2 officers in private meeting that Trump had no idea his supporters were attacking Capitol on January 6, newly obtained audio shows
SUMMARY: During a private meeting last summer, House Minority Leader Kevin McCarthy told two police officers who defended the US Capitol on January 6, 2021, and the mother of a third who later died from his injuries that former President Donald Trump should not be blamed for the violence or waiting hours to call off his supporters who were carrying out the attack, according to newly obtained audio of the conversation.

TITLE: Biden's marijuana move could change lives -- and impact the midterms
SUMMARY: In granting pardons for federal marijuana possession convictions, President Joe Biden is taking a historic step that is likely to be widely popular and could energize core Democratic constituencies just over a month from the midterm elections.

TITLE: Kelly warns 'wheels' could 'come off our democracy' while Masters tries to tie him to Biden in Arizona Senate debate
SUMMARY: While trying to distance himself from his own party, Arizona Democratic Sen. Mark Kelly warned during an hour-long debate on Thursday that the "wheels" could "come off our democracy" if candidates like his GOP opponent, Trump-backed Blake Masters, are elected in November.

TITLE: Several states are sending out inflation relief checks, but some economists say they could further fuel rising prices
SUMMARY: Several states are sending taxpayers money to help them cope with inflation, but some economists warn that the payments will do little to alleviate the pain of rising costs and could further fuel inflation.

TITLE: Shooting outside Rep. Zeldin's home in New York injures 2; family unhurt
SUMMARY: A shooting on the Shirley, New York, property of Rep. Lee Zeldin on Sunday left two injured, the congressman and Republican gubernatorial candidate said in a statement. Zeldin's family was unhurt.

SUMMARY: There is perhaps nowhere in the country where former President Donald Trump had more success elevating his slate of "Make American Great Again" candidates into formidable 2022 contenders than Arizona.

TITLE: Slotkin calls for 'new blood' in Democratic Party but says she will support Biden if he runs in 2024
SUMMARY: Democratic Rep. Elissa Slotkin of Michigan said Sunday the Democratic Party needs "new blood" in Washington, but emphasized her support for President Joe Biden if he decides to run for reelection.

TITLE: Former Gov. Bill Richardson suggests Brittney Griner and Paul Whelan may be released by end of year
